stylometry: A genetic algorithm is used in Evolutionary Solver in an attempt to give the absolute max or min. A genetic algorithm uses a random number simulator to "evolve" or arrive at a smaller data set that has the absolute max or min contained within it. Once it has this small data set it continues to do this until it reaches the optimal solution. Evolutionary solver, if given enough time, can find the optimal solution to a non linear problem, however the time it takes might take months, years, etc. so we can put time constraints on how long it takes which mean it may not give us an optimal solution but it will still provide a good solution. Evolutionary solver also cannot handle many constraints, so problems with constraints may mean that evolutionary solver is not the best way to solve the problem.
